    {
      "id": "t60",
      "tag": "div",
      "text": "Yes — the creator economy continues growing at 20–30% annually. More brands are shifting marketing budgets toward creator partnerships, and new platforms continue expanding monetization tools."
    },
    {
      "id": "t61",
      "tag": "button",
      "text": "Are there too many creators now to succeed?"
    },
    {
      "id": "t62",
      "tag": "div",
      "text": "Competition has increased, but so has the total money in the ecosystem. More brands, more platforms, and more audience demand means the addressable market for creators keeps expanding. Niche specialization is the answer to increased competition."
    },
    {
      "id": "t63",
      "tag": "button",
      "text": "What are the biggest creator economy trends in 2026?"
    },
    {
      "id": "t64",
      "tag": "div",
      "text": "Key trends: AI-assisted content production, short-form video dominance, brand partnership growth, direct fan monetization (memberships and digital products), and multi-platform creator businesses replacing single-platform dependence."
